    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nfollowup work https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/36397#issuecomment-4150379418 : \n\n1. Test coverage could be stronger for the `to_inclusive_pos` logic and edge cases.\n2. `Pos.to_extmark` fetches all buffer lines (`#api.nvim_buf_get_lines(pos.buf, 0, -1, true)`) just to get the line count. Use `nvim_buf_line_count()` instead?\n3. `Range.cursor` signature mismatch with docs. The example won't work as written.\n4. `Range.to_extmark/to_cursor` create temporary `vim.Pos` objects. This partially defeats the performance motivation?\n5. `Range.extmark` validation names: all four `validate()` calls use 'range' as the parameter name instead of the actual parameter names ('start_row', 'start_col', etc.).\n6. Breaking change to `Range.has` semantics: Tests only cover one case (`vim.range(0,0,0,4):has(vim.range(0,0,0,0))`). More edge cases would be valuable.\n7. `intersect` loses `buf`: `Range.new(rs.start_row, rs.start_col, re.end_row, re.end_col)` doesn't pass opts, so the resulting range has no buf even if both inputs had one.\n8. [open question](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/36397#discussion_r3006403327) about `vim.pos` string indexing\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nsee above\n\ncc @TheLeoP ",
